rick315\"/><ref name=\"happymag\"/>\n**[[Personal computer]] (PC)<ref name=\"computerhistory2018\"/><ref name=\"Sridharan\"/><ref name=\"Korec9\">{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/Jacek_Korec_Low_Voltage_Power_MOSFETs/page/n17|title=Low Voltage Power MOSFETs: Design, Performance and Applications|last1=Korec|first1=Jacek|date=2011|publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media]]|isbn=978-1-4419-9320-5|pages=9\u201314}}</ref> \u2014 [[desktop computer]],<ref name=\"tomshardware\"/> [[notebook computer]]<ref name=\"Whiteley\"/><ref name=\"Veendrick337\"/>\n*[[Computer science]]<ref name=\"Mead\">{{cite book|url=http://fennetic.net/irc/Christopher%20R.%20Carroll%20Carver%20Mead%20Mohammed%20Ismail%20Analog%20VLSI%20Implementation%20of%20Neural%20Systems.pdf|title=Analog VLSI Implementation of Neural Systems|date=8 May 1989|publisher=[[Kluwer Academic Publishers]]|isbn=978-1-4613-1639-8|editor-last1=Mead|editor-first1=Carver A.|series=The Kluwer International Series in Engineering and Computer Science|volume=80|location=Norwell, MA|doi=10.1007/978-1-4613-1639-8|editor-last2=Ismail|editor-first2=Mohammed}}</ref>\n**[[Artificial intelligence]] (AI) \u2014 [[neural network]], [[artificial neural network]] (ANN), [[neural processing unit]],<ref name=\"Mead\"/><ref name=\"Holler\">{{cite journal |last1=Holler |first1=M. |last2=Tam |first2=S. |last3=Castro |first3=H. |last4=Benson |first4=R. |title=An electrically trainable artificial neural network (ETANN) with 10240 'floating gate' synapses |journal=Proceedings of the International Joint Conference on Neural Networks |location=Washington, D.C. |year=1989 |volume=2 |pages=191\u2013196 |doi=10.1109/IJCNN.1989.118698}}</ref> feedback and [[feedforward neural networks]], [[maze solving algorithm]]<ref name=\"Mead\"/>\n*[[Computer vision]]<ref name=\"Mead\"/> \u2014 [[optical character recognition]] (OCR),<ref name=\"Klinger\"/> [[augmented reality]] (AR),<ref>{{cite book |last1=Schmalstieg |first1=Dieter |last2=Hollerer |