t. The aircraft has a low trapezoidal wing, empennage in \"T\" configuration, semi-retractable landing gear (mechanical), with the  tailwheel connected to the rudder.\n\nThe aircraft was certificated under JAR-VLA regulations by the Romanian Civil Aviation Authority in November 1999.<ref name=\"JAWA03 p351\">Jackson 2003, p. 351.</ref>\n\n==Variants==\n;IAR 46: baseline production version\n;IAR 46S:More powerful {{convert|73.5|kW|abbr=on}}\n [[Rotax 912 S3]] engine\n\n==Specifications (IAR.46)==\n{{Aircraft specs\n|ref=Brassey's World Aircraft & Systems Directory 1999/2000<ref name=\"Brasseys 99 p455\">Taylor 1999, p.455.</ref>, Jane's all the World's Aircraft 2004-05<ref name=JAWA2004-05>{{cite book |title=Jane's all the World's Aircraft 2004-05 |editor1-last=Jackson |editor1-first=Paul, MRAeS |year=2005 |publisher=Jane''s Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=0-7106-2614-2}}</ref>\n|prime units?=met\n<!--\n        General characteristics\n-->\n|genhide=\n\n|crew=two\n|capacity=\n|length m=7.85\n|span m=11.42\n|height m=2.15\n|wing area sqm=13.87\n|aspect ratio=9.403:1\n|airfoil=GA(W)-1\n|empty weight kg=530\n|empty weight note=\u00b1 5kg\n|gross weight kg=\n|gross weight lb=\n|gross weight note=\n|max takeoff weight kg=750\n|fuel capacity={{convert|78|L|USgal impgal|abbr=on}}\n|more general=\n<!--\n        Powerplant\n-->\n|eng1 number=1\n|eng1 name=[[Rotax 912]] F3/A3\n|eng1 type=4-cylinder horizontally-opposed air-cooled piston engine\n|eng1 kw=58<!-- prop engines -->\n\n|prop blade number=2<!-- propeller aircraft -->\n|prop name=Hoffmann HO-V352F/170FQ\n|prop dia m=1.7\n|prop note=variable-pitch propeller\n\n<!--\n        Performance\n-->\n|max speed kmh=\n|cruise speed kmh=150\n|cruise speed note=(econ cruise)\n|stall speed kmh=78\n|stall speed mph=\n|stall speed kts=\n|stall speed note=\n|never exceed speed kmh=270\n|range km=800\n|range miles=\n|range nmi=\n|range note=(no reserve)\n|ferry range km=\n|ferry range miles=\n|ferry range nmi=\n|ferry range not